The tidyverse

Data analysis and visualization using R 2

Michiel Noback

April 2020

Course contents

Focus of the course

This course has two main focus points:

  • data mangling and explorations
  • data visualizations

The Tidyverse

Background

The tidyverse is an opinionated collection of R packages designed for data science. All packages share an underlying design philosophy, grammar, and data structures.

Hadley Wickham is the driving force behind the tidyverse.

The book

  • There is a book dedicated to the tidyverse: R for Data Science.
  • It is available for free online: https://r4ds.had.co.nz/

Packages

Package listing

Except for readr you will see all of the core packages of the tidyverse:

  • ggplot2: visualization
  • tidyr: tidying
  • dplyr: mangling
  • lubridate: date and time
  • stringr: character data and regex

Old school Data Science

ggplot2

You will learn about the grammar of graphics and how you use a layered architecture to build your plot from data to axis labels and plot theme.

tidyr

Using the functions from the tidyr package you will learn how to clean you data and convert it into tidy format and into other formats.

dplyr

The dplyr package is the Swiss army knife of data mangling. You use it to select, filter, mutate, arrange, summarize and a whole bunch of other operations.

lubridate

Package lubridate makes working with dates and time less gruesome. How do you calculate the passed hours between April 4th 2019, 17:00 PM and May 16 2020, 12:30 AM? (Actually, I would have to look that up as well)

stringr

The stringr package focuses on manipulating and scanning character data.

Disclaimer: knowledge of regex is pretty much essential.
